{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1000,"text":"I want to talk to you a little bit about user-generated content."},{"time":5000,"text":"I'm going to tell you three stories on the way to one argument"},{"time":9000,"text":"that's going to tell you a little bit"},{"time":11000,"text":"about how we open user-generated content up for business."},{"time":15000,"text":"So, here's the first story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"1906. This man, John Philip Sousa, traveled to this place,"},{"time":22000,"text":"the United States Capitol, to talk about this technology,"},{"time":26000,"text":"what he called the, quote, \"talking machines.\""},{"time":30000,"text":"Sousa was not a fan of the talking machines."},{"time":34000,"text":"This is what he had to say."},{"time":35000,"text":"\"These talking machines are going to ruin artistic development"},{"time":39000,"text":"of music in this country."},{"time":40000,"text":"When I was a boy, in front of every house in the summer evenings,"},{"time":45000,"text":"you would find young people together"},{"time":47000,"text":"singing the songs of the day, or the old songs."},{"time":51000,"text":"Today, you hear these infernal machines going night and day."},{"time":57000,"text":"We will not have a vocal chord left,\" Sousa said."},{"time":60000,"text":"\"The vocal chords will be eliminated by a process of evolution"},{"time":64000,"text":"as was the tail of man when he came from the ape.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Now, this is the picture I want you to focus on."},{"time":73000,"text":"This is a picture of culture."},{"time":75000,"text":"We could describe it using modern computer terminology"},{"time":79000,"text":"as a kind of read-write culture."},{"time":82000,"text":"It's a culture where people participate in the creation"},{"time":85000,"text":"and the re-creation of their culture. In that sense, it's read-write."},{"time":90000,"text":"Sousa's fear was that we would lose that capacity"},{"time":95000,"text":"because of these, quote, \"infernal machines.\" They would take it away."},{"time":100000,"text":"And in its place, we'd have the opposite of read-write culture,"},{"time":104000,"text":"what we could call read-only culture."},{"time":107000,"text":"Culture where creativity was consumed"},{"time":110000,"text":"but the consumer is not a creator."},{"time":113000,"text":"A culture which is top-down, owned,"},{"time":116000,"text":"where the vocal chords of the millions have been lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"Now, as you look back at the twentieth century,"},{"time":124000,"text":"at least in what we think of as the, quote, \"developed world\" --"},{"time":129000,"text":"hard not to conclude that Sousa was right."},{"time":132000,"text":"Never before in the history of human culture"},{"time":135000,"text":"had it been as professionalized, never before as concentrated."},{"time":139000,"text":"Never before has creativity of the millions"},{"time":142000,"text":"been as effectively displaced,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and displaced because of these, quote, \"infernal machines.\""},{"time":148000,"text":"The twentieth century was that century"},{"time":150000,"text":"where, at least for those places we know the best,"},{"time":153000,"text":"culture moved from this read-write to read-only existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"So, second. Land is a kind of property --"},{"time":164000,"text":"it is property. It's protected by law."},{"time":168000,"text":"As Lord Blackstone described it, land is protected by trespass law,"},{"time":173000,"text":"for most of the history of trespass law,"},{"time":176000,"text":"by presuming it protects the land all the way down below"},{"time":181000,"text":"and to an indefinite extent upward."},{"time":185000,"text":"Now, that was a pretty good system"},{"time":187000,"text":"for most of the history of the regulation of land,"},{"time":189000,"text":"until this technology came along, and people began to wonder,"},{"time":195000,"text":"were these instruments trespassers"},{"time":198000,"text":"as they flew over land without clearing the rights"},{"time":201000,"text":"of the farms below as they traveled across the country?"},{"time":205000,"text":"Well, in 1945, Supreme Court got a chance to address that question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Two farmers, Thomas Lee and Tinie Causby, who raised chickens,"},{"time":216000,"text":"had a significant complaint because of these technologies."},{"time":220000,"text":"The complaint was that their"},{"time":222000,"text":"chickens followed the pattern of the airplanes"},{"time":225000,"text":"and flew themselves into the walls of the barn"},{"time":229000,"text":"when the airplanes flew over the land."},{"time":231000,"text":"And so they appealed to Lord Blackstone"},{"time":233000,"text":"to say these airplanes were trespassing."},{"time":237000,"text":"Since time immemorial, the law had said,"},{"time":240000,"text":"you can't fly over the land without permission of the landowner,"},{"time":244000,"text":"so this flight must stop."},{"time":248000,"text":"Well, the Supreme Court considered this 100-years tradition"},{"time":253000,"text":"and said, in an opinion written by Justice Douglas,"},{"time":257000,"text":"that the Causbys must lose."},{"time":259000,"text":"The Supreme Court said the doctrine protecting land"},{"time":263000,"text":"all the way to the sky has no place in the modern world,"},{"time":267000,"text":"otherwise every transcontinental flight would"},{"time":271000,"text":"subject the operator to countless trespass suits."},{"time":274000,"text":"Common sense, a rare idea in the law, but here it was. Common sense --"},{"time":279000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":280000,"text":"Revolts at the idea. Common sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Finally. Before the Internet, the last great terror"},{"time":292000,"text":"to rain down on the content industry"},{"time":295000,"text":"was a terror created by this technology. Broadcasting:"},{"time":301000,"text":"a new way to spread content,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and therefore a new battle over the control"},{"time":308000,"text":"of the businesses that would spread content."},{"time":312000,"text":"Now, at that time, the entity,"},{"time":314000,"text":"the legal cartel, that controlled the performance rights"},{"time":318000,"text":"for most of the music that would be broadcast"},{"time":322000,"text":"using these technologies was ASCAP."},{"time":324000,"text":"They had an exclusive license on the most popular content,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and they exercised it in a way that tried to demonstrate"},{"time":332000,"text":"to the broadcasters who really was in charge."},{"time":335000,"text":"So, between 1931 and 1939, they raised rates by some 448 percent,"},{"time":342000,"text":"until the broadcasters finally got together"},{"time":345000,"text":"and said, okay, enough of this."},{"time":347000,"text":"And in 1939, a lawyer, Sydney Kaye, started something"},{"time":350000,"text":"called Broadcast Music Inc. We know it as BMI."},{"time":354000,"text":"And BMI was much more democratic in the art"},{"time":357000,"text":"that it would include within its repertoire,"},{"time":360000,"text":"including African American music for the first time in the repertoire."},{"time":364000,"text":"But most important was that BMI took public domain works"},{"time":369000,"text":"and made arrangements of them, which they gave away for free"},{"time":373000,"text":"to their subscribers. So that in 1940,"},{"time":377000,"text":"when ASCAP threatened to double their rates,"},{"time":381000,"text":"the majority of broadcasters switched to BMI."},{"time":384000,"text":"Now, ASCAP said they didn't care."},{"time":386000,"text":"The people will revolt, they predicted, because the very best music"},{"time":390000,"text":"was no longer available, because they had shifted"},{"time":393000,"text":"to the second best public domain provided by BMI."},{"time":399000,"text":"Well, they didn't revolt, and in 1941, ASCAP cracked."},{"time":405000,"text":"And the important point to recognize"},{"time":408000,"text":"is that even though these broadcasters"},{"time":413000,"text":"were broadcasting something you would call second best,"},{"time":415000,"text":"that competition was enough to break, at that time,"},{"time":420000,"text":"this legal cartel over access to music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"Okay. Three stories. Here's the argument."},{"time":428000,"text":"In my view, the most significant thing to recognize"},{"time":430000,"text":"about what this Internet is doing"},{"time":432000,"text":"is its opportunity to revive the read-write culture"},{"time":436000,"text":"that Sousa romanticized."},{"time":440000,"text":"Digital technology is the opportunity"},{"time":442000,"text":"for the revival of these vocal chords"},{"time":444000,"text":"that he spoke so passionately to Congress about."},{"time":448000,"text":"User-generated content, spreading in businesses"},{"time":452000,"text":"in extraordinarily valuable ways like these,"},{"time":455000,"text":"celebrating amateur culture."},{"time":458000,"text":"By which I don't mean amateurish culture,"},{"time":461000,"text":"I mean culture where people produce"},{"time":464000,"text":"for the love of what they're doing and not for the money."},{"time":468000,"text":"I mean the culture that your kids are producing all the time."},{"time":473000,"text":"For when you think of what Sousa romanticized"},{"time":476000,"text":"in the young people together, singing the songs of the day,"},{"time":479000,"text":"of the old songs, you should recognize"},{"time":481000,"text":"what your kids are doing right now."},{"time":484000,"text":"Taking the songs of the day and the old songs"},{"time":486000,"text":"and remixing them to make them something different."},{"time":490000,"text":"It's how they understand access to this culture."},{"time":493000,"text":"So, let's have some very few examples"},{"time":496000,"text":"to get a sense of what I'm talking about here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"Here's something called Anime Music Video, first example,"},{"time":500000,"text":"taking anime captured from television"},{"time":504000,"text":"re-edited to music tracks."},{"time":506000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":546000,"text":"This one you should be -- confidence. Jesus survives. Don't worry."},{"time":551000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":596000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":604000,"text":"And this is the best."},{"time":606000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":613000,"text":"My love ..."},{"time":617000,"text":"There's only you in my life ..."},{"time":622000,"text":"The only thing that's bright ..."},{"time":628000,"text":"My first love ..."},{"time":633000,"text":"You're every breath that I take ..."},{"time":637000,"text":"You're every step I make ..."},{"time":643000,"text":"And I ...."},{"time":647000,"text":"I want to share all my love with you ..."},{"time":658000,"text":"No one else will do ..."},{"time":663000,"text":"And your eyes ..."},{"time":667000,"text":"They tell me how much you care ..."},{"time":673000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":678000,"text":"So, this is remix, right?"},{"time":680000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":686000,"text":"And it's important to emphasize that what this is not"},{"time":688000,"text":"is not what we call, quote, \"piracy.\""},{"time":691000,"text":"I'm not talking about nor justifying"},{"time":694000,"text":"people taking other people's content in wholesale"},{"time":697000,"text":"and distributing it without the permission of the copyright owner."},{"time":700000,"text":"I'm talking about people taking and recreating"},{"time":703000,"text":"using other people's content, using digital technologies"},{"time":707000,"text":"to say things differently."},{"time":709000,"text":"Now, the importance of this"},{"time":710000,"text":"is not the technique that you've seen here."},{"time":714000,"text":"Because, of course, every technique that you've seen here"},{"time":716000,"text":"is something that television and film producers"},{"time":718000,"text":"have been able to do for the last 50 years."},{"time":720000,"text":"The importance is that that technique has been democratized."},{"time":725000,"text":"It is now anybody with access to a $1,500 computer"},{"time":730000,"text":"who can take sounds and images from the culture around us"},{"time":732000,"text":"and use it to say things differently."},{"time":734000,"text":"These tools of creativity have become tools of speech."},{"time":739000,"text":"It is a literacy for this generation. This is how our kids speak."},{"time":746000,"text":"It is how our kids think. It is what your kids are"},{"time":751000,"text":"as they increasingly understand digital technologies"},{"time":755000,"text":"and their relationship to themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"Now, in response to this new use of culture using digital technologies,"},{"time":765000,"text":"the law has not greeted this Sousa revival"},{"time":769000,"text":"with very much common sense."},{"time":771000,"text":"Instead, the architecture of copyright law"},{"time":774000,"text":"and the architecture of digital technologies,"},{"time":776000,"text":"as they interact, have produced the presumption"},{"time":779000,"text":"that these activities are illegal."},{"time":782000,"text":"Because if copyright law at its core regulates something called copies,"},{"time":785000,"text":"then in the digital world the one fact we can't escape"},{"time":788000,"text":"is that every single use of culture produces a copy."},{"time":793000,"text":"Every single use therefore requires permission;"},{"time":796000,"text":"without permission, you are a trespasser."},{"time":799000,"text":"You're a trespasser with about as much sense"},{"time":801000,"text":"as these people were trespassers."},{"time":806000,"text":"Common sense here, though, has not yet revolted"},{"time":810000,"text":"in response to this response that the law has offered"},{"time":813000,"text":"to these forms of creativity."},{"time":816000,"text":"Instead, what we've seen"},{"time":817000,"text":"is something much worse than a revolt."},{"time":821000,"text":"There's a growing extremism that comes from both sides"},{"time":825000,"text":"in this debate, in response to this conflict"},{"time":828000,"text":"between the law and the use of these technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"One side builds new technologies, such as one recently announced"},{"time":835000,"text":"that will enable them"},{"time":838000,"text":"to automatically take down from sites like YouTube"},{"time":841000,"text":"any content that has any copyrighted content in it,"},{"time":843000,"text":"whether or not there's a judgment of fair use"},{"time":846000,"text":"that might be applied to the use of that content."},{"time":848000,"text":"And on the other side, among our kids,"},{"time":851000,"text":"there's a growing copyright abolitionism,"},{"time":855000,"text":"a generation that rejects the very notion"},{"time":858000,"text":"of what copyright is supposed to do, rejects copyright"},{"time":861000,"text":"and believes that the law is nothing more than an ass"},{"time":864000,"text":"to be ignored and to be fought at every opportunity possible."},{"time":871000,"text":"The extremism on one side begets extremism on the other,"},{"time":875000,"text":"a fact we should have learned many, many times over,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and both extremes in this debate are just wrong."},{"time":883000,"text":"Now, the balance that I try to fight for,"},{"time":887000,"text":"I, as any good liberal, try to fight for first"},{"time":889000,"text":"by looking to the government. Total mistake, right?"},{"time":893000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"Looked first to the courts and the legislatures to try to get them"},{"time":897000,"text":"to do something to make the system make more sense."},{"time":899000,"text":"It failed partly because the courts are too passive,"},{"time":903000,"text":"partly because the legislatures are corrupted,"},{"time":905000,"text":"by which I don't mean that there's bribery"},{"time":908000,"text":"operating to stop real change,"},{"time":911000,"text":"but more the economy of influence that governs how Congress functions"},{"time":915000,"text":"means that policymakers here will not understand this"},{"time":919000,"text":"until it's too late to fix it."},{"time":921000,"text":"So, we need something different, we need a different kind of solution."},{"time":925000,"text":"And the solution here, in my view, is a private solution,"},{"time":929000,"text":"a solution that looks to legalize what it is to be young again,"},{"time":933000,"text":"and to realize the economic potential of that,"},{"time":935000,"text":"and that's where the story of BMI becomes relevant."},{"time":939000,"text":"Because, as BMI demonstrated, competition here"},{"time":942000,"text":"can achieve some form of balance. The same thing can happen now."},{"time":947000,"text":"We don't have a public domain to draw upon now,"},{"time":950000,"text":"so instead what we need is two types of changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"First, that artists and creators embrace the idea,"},{"time":957000,"text":"choose that their work be made available more freely."},{"time":961000,"text":"So, for example, they can say their work is available freely"},{"time":964000,"text":"for non-commercial, this amateur-type of use,"},{"time":966000,"text":"but not freely for any commercial use."},{"time":968000,"text":"And second, we need the businesses"},{"time":971000,"text":"that are building out this read-write culture"},{"time":974000,"text":"to embrace this opportunity expressly, to enable it,"},{"time":979000,"text":"so that this ecology of free content, or freer content,"},{"time":984000,"text":"can grow on a neutral platform"},{"time":986000,"text":"where they both exist simultaneously,"},{"time":989000,"text":"so that more-free can compete with less-free,"},{"time":994000,"text":"and the opportunity to develop the creativity in that competition"},{"time":998000,"text":"can teach one the lessons of the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001000,"text":"Now, I would talk about one particular such plan"},{"time":1005000,"text":"that I know something about,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"but I don't want to violate TED's first commandment of selling,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"so I'm not going to talk about this at all."},{"time":1011000,"text":"I'm instead just going to remind you of the point that BMI teaches us."},{"time":1018000,"text":"That artist choice is the key for new technology"},{"time":1023000,"text":"having an opportunity to be open for business,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"and we need to build artist choice here"},{"time":1029000,"text":"if these new technologies are to have that opportunity."},{"time":1032000,"text":"But let me end with something I think much more important --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"much more important than business."},{"time":1037000,"text":"It's the point about how this connects to our kids."},{"time":1040000,"text":"We have to recognize they're different from us. This is us, right?"},{"time":1045000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1046000,"text":"We made mixed tapes; they remix music."},{"time":1048000,"text":"We watched TV; they make TV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"It is technology that has made them different,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"and as we see what this technology can do,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"we need to recognize you can't kill"},{"time":1060000,"text":"the instinct the technology produces. We can only criminalize it."},{"time":1064000,"text":"We can't stop our kids from using it."},{"time":1066000,"text":"We can only drive it underground."},{"time":1068000,"text":"We can't make our kids passive again."},{"time":1071000,"text":"We can only make them, quote, \"pirates.\" And is that good?"},{"time":1076000,"text":"We live in this weird time. It's kind of age of prohibitions,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"where in many areas of our life,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"we live life constantly against the law."},{"time":1085000,"text":"Ordinary people live life against the law,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"and that's what I -- we are doing to our kids."},{"time":1091000,"text":"They live life knowing they live it against the law."},{"time":1095000,"text":"That realization is extraordinarily corrosive,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"extraordinarily corrupting."},{"time":1102000,"text":"And in a democracy, we ought to be able to do better."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Do better, at least for them, if not for opening for business."},{"time":1113000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1114000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}